Algoirthm:

1. Start
2. Define macro variable for pi
3. Declare & initalize the varibales result & r of type float
4 Claculate the circumference of the circle using 2,pi,r
5. Store the calulated resultant value in result variable
6. print the result value in console
7. return null value
8. end

#include <stdio.h>
#define pi 3.142
int main()
{
float result, r=2.3;
result=2*pi*r;
printf("%d",result);
return 0;
}
